# NAS Infrastructure

- **Red-zone:** production NAS deploy (`redeploy-ultra.sh`, `sync-to-nas.sh` against live host) requires explicit human approval.
- Compose overlays are additive — do not remove `compose.ultra-udp.yaml` or `compose.ultra-udp-host.yaml` without ADR.
- Required flags: `RA2_COMPOSE_ULTRA=1`, `RA2_COMPOSE_ULTRA_UDP=1`, `RA2_COMPOSE_ULTRA_UDP_HOST=1`.
- Never deploy from a branch that has not passed `run-deploy-tests.sh`.
- Coturn host network changes require security review — invoke `nas-webrtc-verify` skill.
- Invoke `nas-deploy-ultra` skill before any deploy task.
- Invoke `nas-storage-boundary` skill before path or sync changes.

## Verify (dev worktree, pre-approval)

```bash
sh scripts/run-deploy-tests.sh
```

## Verify (post-deploy — red, NAS only)

```bash
sh scripts/verify-deployment.sh
```
